<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.203/172: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-05T15:00:00-04:00">December
                                    5, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1565. Department’s no. 1200, October 6, 10 p.m. Please report what
                            progress has been made in negotiating an informal agreement with the
                            Egyptian authorities according to American military authorities
                            exclusive jurisdiction in criminal matters over military personnel.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>